These are Puzzles for 2x4 Level 8

.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-8-1::.
4 different games are played: scrabble, monopoly, poker, snooker
There are 4 different nationalities: nigerian, australian, malaysian, mexican
1. the person playing poker is between the malaysian and the australian##2
2. the person playing snooker is on the left or right of the malaysian##3
3. the malaysian is not to the left of the malaysian##8
4. the australian is not the person playing poker##6
5. the person playing poker is somewhere to the right of the person playing scrabble##5
6. the person playing scrabble is on the right of the nigerian##1

.:: Answer ::.
|         |    1     |    2    |    3    |   4    |
| Game   | snooker  | scrabble | poker | monopoly  |
| Nationality   | nigerian | malaysian   | mexican  | australian |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-8-2::.
House: modern, art-deco, gothic-revival, palace
The people's birthday is in 4 different months: february, november, april, june
1. the person who's birthday is in june is not to the left of the person who's birthday is in june##8
2. the modern house is somewhere to the right of the palace house##5
3. the modern house is the person who's birthday is in november##1
4. the palace house is between the modern house and the art-deco house##2
5. the art-deco house is somewhere between the gothic-revival house and the person who's birthday is in february##7
6. the person who's birthday is in april is somewhere to the left of the art-deco house##5
7. the person who's birthday is in february is not to the left of the person who's birthday is in february##8

.:: Answer ::.
|        |     1      |        2        |    3     |     4      |
| House   | gothic-revival | art-deco          | palace | modern     |
| Birthday    | april      | june | february | november |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-8-3::.
The people prefer 4 different types of sport: parkour, rugby, baseball, climbing
4 different games are played: domino, poker, mah-jongg, snooker
1. the person playing domino is not to the left of the person who's sport is baseball##8
2. the person playing poker is on the far left##1
3. the person who's sport is rugby is on the right of the person who's sport is parkour##1
4. the person who's sport is rugby is in an even position##4
5. the person who's sport is climbing is on the far left or far right##3
6. the person who's sport is parkour is somewhere to the left of the person playing snooker##5
7. the person who's sport is climbing is the person playing mah-jongg##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1     |      2      |     3     |     4     |
| Sport           | parkour | rugby | baseball     | climbing |
| Game   | poker    | snooker   | domino | mah-jongg    |

