.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-8-6::.
The people use 4 different means of transport: train, skateboard, taxi, roller
City: liverpool, prague, san-francisco, hannover
1. the person traveling to hannover is on the left of the person traveling to san-francisco##1
2. the person traveling to prague is somewhere to the left of the person driving the train##5
3. the person driving the taxi is on the right of the person traveling to san-francisco##1
4. the person traveling to liverpool is on the left or right of the person traveling to san-francisco##3
5. the person driving the train is somewhere to the left of the person driving the skateboard##5
6. the person driving the roller is not to the left of the person traveling to prague##8
7. the person driving the roller is the person traveling to prague##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1     |      2      |   3   |    4    |
| Transport          | roller | train | skateboard  | taxi |
| City   | prague   | hannover         | san-francisco | liverpool |

